'Braunschweig' or 'Brunswick' (; Low German: Brunswiek ; "Brunswick"
(definition 2), The American Heritage Dictionary p. 245 3d. ed. 1992 ), is
a city of 250,556 people, [http://www1.nls.niedersac-
hsen.de/statistik/html/parametereingabe.asp?DT=K1000014&CM=Bev%F6lkerungsfortsc-
hreibung "BevÃ¶lkerungsfortschreibung"] (in German). Landesbetrieb fÃ¼r Statistik
und Kommunikationstechnologie Niedersachsen. December 31, 2011. Accessed August
5, 2012. located in the state of Lower Saxony, Germany. It is located
north of the Harz mountains at the farthest navigable point of the Oker river,
which connects to the North Sea via the rivers Aller and Weser.
